
ssh-keygen - This command generates the public and private keys for the ssh connections 
 if not specified it goes to the files id_rsa and id_rsa.public

ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub user@(IP) - This command send the key to a users system which allowes
 you to access said system in future without needing a password or verification

ssh user@(IP) - this command allowes you to ssh into another users account as long as
  you have their password as it will always ask for one.

